# Dropdown Integration - Quick Visual Guide

## What Changed?

### Before: TextBox (Free Text Entry)
```
???????????????????????????????????????????
? party name: [ABC Company________]       ? ? User types anything
? item:       [Bearing____________]       ? ? Typos possible
???????????????????????????????????????????

Problems:
? Typos: "ABC Comapny", "Bareing"
? Duplicates: "ABC Company" vs "ABC Co."
? Invalid entries: Non-existent parties
? Inconsistent data
```

### After: ComboBox (Dropdown Selection)
```
???????????????????????????????????????????
? party name: [ABC Company      ?]        ? ? Click for list
?             ?? ABC Company              ?
?             ?? XYZ Industries           ?
?             ?? Smith & Sons             ?
?                                          ?
? item:       [Bearing          ?]        ? ? Click for list
?             ?? Bearing                  ?
?             ?? Bolt                     ?
?             ?? Gasket                   ?
???????????????????????????????????????????

Benefits:
? No typos possible
? Only valid parties/items
? Consistent naming
? AutoComplete search
? Active items only
```

## How to Use

### Method 1: Click and Select
```
1. Click on dropdown arrow [?]
2. Scroll through list
3. Click on desired party/item
4. Selection appears in field
```

### Method 2: Type to Search (AutoComplete)
```
1. Click in the dropdown field
2. Start typing: "A" 
   ? Dropdown filters to items starting with "A"
3. Continue typing: "AB"
   ? Further narrows down
4. Select from filtered list or press Enter
```

### Method 3: Add New Item On-the-Fly
```
1. Click "Manage Parties" or "Manage Items" button
2. Add new entry in master form
3. Close master form
4. Return to main form
5. Dropdown automatically updated ?
6. Select newly added item
```

